# Rocq project file for Ascent runtime optimization correctness proofs
#
# Verifies correctness of four performance optimizations applied to
# the PraTTaIL Ascent runtime code generator:
#
#   Opt 2. TLS Vec Pool Equivalence     (iteration produces same elements)
#   Opt 3. Dead Rule Pruning            (unreachable rules derive nothing)
#   Opt 4. OrdVar / Scope Ordering      (total order / total preorder)
#   Opt 5. SCC Splitting                (Core fixpoint = Full restriction)
#
# Dependency order:
#   Prelude.v              — Hash model, list utilities
#   GraphReachability.v    — Directed graph, transitive closure (Opts 3, 5)
#   TLSPoolEquiv.v         — Opt 2 (standalone, depends only on Prelude)
#   TotalOrder.v           — Opt 4 (standalone, depends only on Prelude)
#   DeadRulePruning.v      — Opt 3 (depends on GraphReachability)
#   SCCSplitting.v         — Opt 5 (depends on GraphReachability, DeadRulePruning)
#   ConcreteInstantiations.v — Calculator / RhoCalc instances (depends on all)

-Q theories AscentOptimizations

# Source files (dependency order)
theories/Prelude.v
theories/GraphReachability.v
theories/TLSPoolEquiv.v
theories/TotalOrder.v
theories/DeadRulePruning.v
theories/SCCSplitting.v
theories/ConcreteInstantiations.v
